The ASHBOURNE. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. March 12, 1903.) No. 133. Appeal from the District Court of the United States for the Southern District of New York. Pierre M. Brown, for appellant. Le Boy S. Gove, for appellee.

Before WALLACE, LACOMBE, and COXE, Circuit Judges.

No opinion. Decree affirmed, with interest and costs. See (D. C.) 112 Fed. 687.
